Those of you who don't like the IGB, not much that can be done to change your opinion of it, since you've known nothing else.  You're like the boy in the bubble imho (a bit extreme, but you get the point), sheltered from the chaos the server could, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  would</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be without it.<br>
<br>
The IGB was created to deal with trakanon and Venril Sathir in the early days of RoK, for 3, yes, 3 guilds.  No one else could kill those mobs at that time, and rather than continue to have racing and other bs happening, the IGB came into place.  <br>
Did it have to expand to allow other guilds onto it?  No.  <br>
Did it though?  Yes.  <br>
Has it refused a guild admittance to it?  No.  <br>
Has it asked that guilds use some common sense about what they are capable of before coming there?  Absolutely.  <br>
Has any guild there been refused a rotation slot?  No.  <br>
Have they been encouraged to try other things first?  Yes in a couple of cases.  <br>
Was it malicious?  No.  <br>
Was it realistic based on experience?  Maybe.  Probably, imho.<br>
<br>
Is this going to change the way people like Epiphany feel about it?  Not likely, but I can hope. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15408">Quintall Dys'Raydin</a><BR>
