From a GL point of view, I remerber this from 2 points of reference.<br>
<br>
In the old days VH was surpassed only by SoN, Hoss, and ML. We would view others as folks that had to wait their turn.  We would bring guests (under 5).<br>
<br>
Later, months later, we reformed and many were above us, TR, IG, L'Malla, etc, and we just wanted that piece of the pie.<br>
<br>
When those folks wanted Inno or CT, they would contact us and work it out, and/or post it.<br>
<br>
The same communication should prevail now, I knew on that 2nd incarnation we couldnt do CT, and I couldn't begrudge those who could. So I bartered the best deal I could for my members on conflict nights, and told them to like it or leave and raked in the loot for them. Not the best situation....just the best I could get.  EQ IS survival of the fittest, bargain what you can, grow while can, and hope for the best.<br>
